<center><div class="jumbotron">
  <h1><font color="#00BFFF"><b>HOW TO CHANGE WIPER BLADES</b></font></h1>
</div>

<!--Write in the steps-->

<ul class="list-group">
  <li class="list-group-item">1.) Locate the rubber part of the wiper blade and buy the replacement for the blade.  <p>You will need to measure the old rubber blades to refer to at the auto parts store.</a></li>
  <li class="list-group-item">2.) Raise the metal wiper arm away from the windshield.  It should hold steady near <p>perpendicular to the windshield.</a></li>
  <li class="list-group-item">3.) There should be a small plastic stopper where the rubber wiper meets the metal <p>arm.  Press the stopper and unhook the old rubber blade from the metal arm</a></li>
  <li class="list-group-item">4.) Slide the new wiper into the same end of the arm that you pulled the old wiper out <p>of.  Pivot the wiper until it snaps into place and lay the metal arm back against the <p>windshield.</a></li>
  <li class="list-group-item">5.) Repeat for the other wiper.</a></li>
</ul>

<h2>Are you a visual learner?</h2>
